4 The shop was owned by an old man named Elias Windcroft, a clockmaker with silver hair and eyes that always seemed to be counting something. He rarely spoke, and when he did, his words were deliberate and weighted, like he was always answering a question asked long ago. No one knew where Elias had come from, only that he had been in the town longer than most of its buildings.
